data.chText: 不完美的；有错误的；有缺陷的
data.enText: not perfect; not working or made correctly

data.chText: 商品如有缺陷，可要求退款。
data.enText: Ask for a refund if the goods are faulty.
an accident caused by a faulty signal
wrong or containing mistakes, often resulting in bad decisions

simple_means.memory_skill: fault 错误；欺骗 + y …的 → 有错误的，有缺点的

tr: not agreeing with a model or not following established rules
the wrong side of the road"

example: I returned the appliance because it was defective

value.def: A faulty piece of equipment has something wrong with it and is not working properly.

example.ex: The money will be used to repair faulty equipment.
example.tran: 这笔钱将用来修理出故障的设备。

value.tran: (设备等)有问题的，有毛病的,出故障的

value.def: If you describe someone's argument or reasoning as faulty, you mean that it is wrong or contains mistakes, usually because they have not been thinking in a logical way.

example.ex: Their interpretation was faulty — they had misinterpreted things.
example.tran: 他们的理解是错误的——他们将事情曲解了。

value.tran: (论证或推理)错误的，谬误的,不完善的

rootsaffixes.indicate: = err, to deceive 错误；欺骗
rootsaffixes.title: fall, fail, fals, fault

partsOfSpeech.dec: de 加强 + fault 错误；欺骗 → 重大欺骗 → 违约
fail 错误；欺骗 + ing 行为的产物 → 错误之处 → 缺点
fail 错误；欺骗 + ure 行为 → 错误状态 → 失败
fall 错误；欺骗 + acious 有…性质的 → 犯错误的
fall 错误；欺骗 + acy 表情况 → 错误；谬论
fall 错误；欺骗 + ible 能…的 → 能出错误的 → 易错的
false 错误 + hood 表性质 → 虚伪；错误
fals 错误；欺骗 + ification 形成… → 伪造；曲解
fals 错误；欺骗 + ify 使 → 篡改；欺骗
fault 错误；欺骗 + less 无…的 → 无错误的，无缺点的
fault 错误；欺骗 + y …的 → 有错误的，有缺点的
in 无 + fallible 易错的 → 无可指责的
un 不，无，没有 + failing 缺点，短处 → 不会出错的 → （永远）可靠的
partsOfSpeech.d: 经久不衰的；（永远）可靠的
